<subSubSection id="6525A372F1E2A3F537AAF7E45B88BA58" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E66E849CBE131E658F579827AF9FA4ED" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574C2105770ABB6E25734CE7E75097E9" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicName id="A487BBD38B084AA9199397070AF4D675" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora" order="Diaporthales" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Sheathospora</taxonomicName>
(Lat.): referring to the conidia with distinct hyaline sheath.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F0EC93671750CC66F342B120C4EB6E94" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FD72DDE981A36F261A084753A36FD4E8" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="356711A4EB1FC73F2EA89FEB94AD3369" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">
This genus differs from other genera in 
<taxonomicName id="505EF14AB1BD0752B502ABF775A87706" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" rank="family">Melanconiellaceae</taxonomicName>
by conical and discrete pycnidia with aseptate, cylindrical to ellipsoidal conidia with distinct hyaline sheath.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E38872A4C91D476A86DC6CED3DC54DC1" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" type="type species">
<paragraph id="BA4905C8A626610F347D394C3F93AB6F" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6CC6C39AECBB0599CDC95E23E19EBC7F" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicName id="CED2B88CC0B1151C0C17AE292D11F400" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora cornuta" order="Diaporthales" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">Sheathospora cornuta</taxonomicName>
(C.M. Tian &amp; Z. Du) Fan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9415E634FEA9BFB1F6E5864A04E596A0" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="17" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph id="797D22C10D239D03EF97F861F371B62E" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">Descriptions.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EAA1A5B0056967D7EE02D3589D3A4AAC" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="17" pageNumber="106">
Conidiomata pycnidial, immersed in host bark, erumpent through the surface of host branches. Ectostromatic disc inconspicuous and ex 
<pageBreakToken id="40B4B99C980FFA0D9392BADDBAC70F82" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" start="start">tended</pageBreakToken>
to form a beak at maturity. Central column absent. Conidiophores hyaline, smooth, cylindrical, simple, rarely branched at the base. Conidiogenous cells hyaline, phialidic. Conidia hyaline, aseptate, with distinct hyaline sheath. Sexual morph was not observed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84ED9E4BBD39FDA5C3447136C18B8DA4" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" type="notes">
<paragraph id="3239B8A6723F5984FE1F681CDF00DCD1" pageId="18" pageNumber="107">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FBB905B7756C9C6B0B027F0E20477588" pageId="18" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="751B758DACD65B2C66BC34111369A8AE" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Sheathospora</taxonomicName>
is established for 
<taxonomicName id="6FA61E0BD5FC813BCEBF36B88E5699C7" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella cornuta" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">Melanconiella cornuta</taxonomicName>
, which was previously included in the 
<taxonomicName id="73F36B30D9D5C41C073828C9020D954B" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
clade (
<bibRefCitation id="AEED7C2F74D9B468C98D340A35908EF9" author="Voglmayr, H" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 44" title="Multigene phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Melanconiella (Diaporthales)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-012-0175-8" volume="57" year="2012">Voglmayr et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B5447F13C20529E2A33057FD39E20E6E" author="Du, Z" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="252 - 260" title="Host and geographic range extensions of Melanconiella, with a new species M. cornuta in China." url="http://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.327.3.4" volume="327" year="2017">Du et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Morphologically, it differs from other genera in 
<taxonomicName id="0755299CE3D5CF37F421C50672A1642C" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" rank="family">Melanconiellaceae</taxonomicName>
by pycnidial conidiomata and conidia with distinct hyaline sheath. In our phylogenetic analyses, 
<taxonomicName id="5B56401AD5A3B8B8E76CF8E9A25B1CC3" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella cornuta" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cornuta">Melanconiella cornuta</taxonomicName>
formed a distinct clade basal to 
<taxonomicName id="EB9802161AD1C74E9D8B3C5E2131F298" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName id="D63BBF229E3CC25943967C368BBE5A06" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" rank="family">Melanconiellaceae</taxonomicName>
. Based on morphology and different hosts (
<taxonomicName id="A3C95E9E3D0ABE0DC0EE321C39FBA8A9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cornaceae" genus="Cornus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cornus" order="Cornales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Cornus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E58A09BCE76E65DAC9BA5FDEE6C41BA8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Juglans" order="Fagales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Juglans</taxonomicName>
vs. 
<taxonomicName id="348827DD57616C05B10171FA71425929" family="Betulaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
), it is here excluded from 
<taxonomicName id="35EBAB79C0A07B33DE457FCAD224491C" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
and transferred to the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="D44E1C0A059EB4F0181AE8AA35DD1B02" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora." order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Sheathospora.</taxonomicName>
In our revised circumscription, 
<taxonomicName id="2E1CDCF6F1883D3D23C5CE25BBD8F8BE" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" rank="family">Melanconiellaceae</taxonomicName>
include three genera named 
<taxonomicName id="B8EB3178F735531839D0EB1E5AB8E657" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconiella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconiella</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="19D37D8BF5297603CFAA47FB698E4EC7" class="Sordariomycetes" genus="Microascospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microascospora" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Microascospora</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="32CA43D37E881895363B4BCE4E16BDC1" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconiellaceae" genus="Sheathospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sheathospora" order="Diaporthales" pageId="18" pageNumber="107" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Sheathospora</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
